  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      40 patients with the diagnosis of major depression are included. There are two interventions:
      partial sleep deprivation (PSD) and normal night sleep (CTRL). Patients are randomly assigned
      to PSD-(2 undisturbed nights)-CTRL or CTRL-(2 undisturbed nights)-PSD. Cytokine-status,
      neuropsychological and psychopathometric status are assessed pre and post each interventional
      and control condition.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
